tion etc etc. THAT is just ridiculous. Really people, let kids be kids, let them go to kindergarten when they're 4 or 5 (it's 5 here) on time, or when they're ready. I do not get all this competition to have the smart kid, but by cheating or putting their that child's emotions to the wayside to do so. A friend of mine does her child's homework for her so that's correct...I have voiced my displeasure and how I really *really* think this is only going to hurt her child in the long run, but to no avail. She obviously doesn't feel her child is smart enough to pass by on her own merit...and one day, her little girl is going to figure that out, how will she feel then? "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="978" language="en" documentId="5068" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Jodi" date="03/19/2012" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://www.circleofmoms.com/debating-mums/redshirting-for-kindergarten-688687" topic="redshirting" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="5068" notes="" title="Redshirting for Kindergarten?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="978"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>